# JavaScript Course – Beginner to Advanced

## 📌 Introduction
JavaScript (JS) is one of the most popular and versatile programming languages in the world.  
It is the **backbone of web development**, enabling developers to make websites interactive, dynamic, and user-friendly.

- **Created by:** Brendan Eich in 1995
- **Type:** High-level, interpreted, multi-paradigm language
- **Runs on:** Browsers (Frontend) & Servers (via Node.js)
- **Role in MERN Stack:**  
  - **M**ongoDB → Database  
  - **E**xpress.js → Backend Framework  
  - **R**eact.js → Frontend Library  
  - **N**ode.js → JS Runtime for backend  

---

## 📜 JavaScript Versions
JavaScript has evolved over the years. Key updates are released through **ECMAScript (ES)** versions.

- **ES5 (2009):** Standardized JS, added strict mode, JSON support.
- **ES6 / ES2015:** Introduced `let`, `const`, arrow functions, classes, template literals, destructuring, modules, promises.
- **ES7 / ES2016:** Added `**` operator, `Array.prototype.includes`.
- **ES8 / ES2017:** `async/await`, Object methods.
- **ES9 / ES2018:** Rest/Spread in objects, async iteration.
- **ES10 / ES2019:** `Array.flat()`, optional catch binding.
- **ES11 / ES2020:** Nullish coalescing (`??`), optional chaining (`?.`).
- **ES12 / ES2021+:** Logical assignment operators, Promise.any, WeakRefs.

---

## 💡 Use Cases of JavaScript
JavaScript is **everywhere**:
- 🌐 **Frontend Development** → DOM manipulation, animations, event handling.
- 🖥 **Backend Development** → Build servers with Node.js and Express.
- 📱 **Mobile App Development** → React Native, Ionic.
- 🖥 **Desktop Applications** → Electron.js.
- 🎮 **Game Development** → Phaser.js, Three.js.
- 🤖 **AI & Machine Learning** → TensorFlow.js.
- 🛠 **Automation & Scripting** → CLI tools, web scraping.

